As @tbl-Left-Right-General-Results highlight, the average fixation duration and number of fixations across the left and right topics were fairly close across all trials. Where @fig-densityplot further illustrates the closeness of the eye-tracking values across the two opposing topics across trials throughout both selections.  Through an one-way ANOVA test , it was confirmed that the selection of a topic on the left or right did not influence the response time in a meaningful way (`r anova_print`). However , a one-way anova test show that participants fixated more on the topic that they selected (`r anova_print2`). @fig-densityplot confirms this finding , as the mean fixation value of the chosen topic is higher than the unchosen one in both scenarios. 

